  • Method Details

    • uuid

      String uuid()
      The UUID of the model. This does not change
      Returns:
      The UUID of the model

    • database

      Database database()
      The database, or table that the model is the child of. This is also referred to as the parent of the model.
      Returns:
      The Database object of the table

    • table

      String table()
      The table the migration will be run on inside the parent
      Returns:
      The name of the table in the parent database

    • columns

      ArrayList<Column> columns()
      The columns that will appear in order and in the specified parent
      Returns:
      An arraylist of column objects the contain the information of the column

    • name

      String name()
      The name of the model, used in the initialization of the database and debugging
      Returns:
      The name of the model as a string

    • version

      String version()
      The version of the model, should be updated when changes have been made to the model that require a database migration.

      The version should be in the format of "major.minor.patch" (e.g. "7.7.2")

      Returns:
      The version of the model as a string

    • populate

      void populate() throws SQLException
      The method used to populate a row of data with this model in the table
      Throws:
      SQLException

    • automaticallyMigrate

      default boolean automaticallyMigrate()
      Whether the model should be migrated automatically upon creation or a modification.
      Returns:
      A boolean representing if it should be able to automatically migrate. This is by default false.

    • migratedVersion

      default String migratedVersion()
      Gets the migrated version that has been last used for a model
      Returns:
      The version as a String type. -1 is returned upon no row being found.

    • migrate

      default void migrate(boolean init)
      Migrates the model on a table and creates the columns by default
      Parameters:
      init - Whether this is the initial round of migration and will migrate the model

    • revert

      default void revert()
      Reverts the migration to the specified state

      This has no action by default as it can be intrusive to assume actions.
